3:22 PM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Felicia E Armstrong appeared by video, in custody from FC jail. Called 22CF18 and 22CF21. Here on request from Armstrong for bail/bond reduction. Court reviews case and indicates SPD is working on obtaining an attorney. Court questions Armstrong on what treatment plan she has in place. Armstrong does not have a plan set up yet. Court questions Armstrong. State questions if she has any other source of income. Armstrong responds. State objects to reduction of bond in each case, unless a treatment plan is set up with proof. Court questions prior attorney. Armstrong responds. Court continues bond on 22CF18 and on 22CF21 reduces bond to $1000 cash. Bond can be addressed again, if Armstrong can provide verification that she will be attending treatment through the Health and Wellness Center with condition that she continue with treatment and remain at address with her mother.
